    #include <stdio.h>
    #include <inttypes.h> 
    int y=2, x=1;
    int main() {
      uintptr_t p = (uintptr_t)(&x + 1);
      uintptr_t q = (uintptr_t)&y;
      printf("Addresses: p=%" PRIxPTR " q=%" PRIxPTR "\n",
             p,q);
      _Bool b = (p==q);
      // can this be false even with identical addresses?
      printf("(p==q) = %s\n", b?"true":"false");
      return 0;
    }
